						               													<description>In Panzer Squadron each player takes control of a number of miniature tanks. The game is played on a modular playing board made out of hexes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each tank has an associated game card made up of 2 sides. One side gives the history and technical specifications of the tank; the other side provides information necessary to play Panzer Squadron.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player takes 15 Tiles and places them on the game-play mat in turns. Then each player places their tanks on a hexagon bordering their side of the game-play mat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1) Throw a 10-sided dice (D10) to determine which player has initiative that turn. The player with the highest roll controls the initiative. &amp;#10;2) The player who controls the initiative chooses one of their tanks and activates it.&amp;#10;3) The other player then chooses one of their tanks and activates it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When You Activate A Tank You May Choose One Of Four Actions: &amp;#10;-Move the tank&amp;#10;-Fire on another tank&amp;#10;-Move the tank and fire on another tank &amp;#10;-Leave the tank in its current position to ambush passing tanks&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Winner is the player who has tanks left at the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Home Page: http://www.panzersquadron.com/&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
